+++++++++++++++++++++++++++ Build Angular Project +++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 

-> Download Node JS and install. Then copy file location path - C:\Program Files\nodejs and add in Environment variables.
		--> open cmd and check "node -v" and "npm -v" version - is these installed or not.
		
-> Install Angular CLI :- open terminal and run:
		--> $ npm install -g @angular/cli  
			--> Check installation :- $ ng version 
			--> if getting error while installing npm then check Environment variables - npm path is added in System variables or not.
			
-> Go to project directory and open cmd in project folder.
		--> npm install // build angular project
		--> $ ng serve //Run Angular Project
	
+++++++++++++++++++++++++++ Build Java Project +++++++++++++++++++++++++++

--> first install Maven :- and check in cmd - $ mvn --version
		--> if getting error then check Environment Paths -> Add MAVEN_HOME and PATH in Environment variables


--> open cmd from project directory and build :-
	--> $ npm build
	--> $ ng build --configuration production		// this will create :- "dist/" folder     // Angular Project Build Complete
	
---> Install nginx on EC2
	--> $ yum install nginx -y
	--> $ systemctl start nginx
	--> $ systemctl enable nginx
	
	
	
===============> I build angular project locally - dist/ folder and now i want to move this folder to EC2 instance using WinSCP software
	--> /home/ec2-user/valuation-management-system-app/browser ===> Main Angular files are inside so Now copy them to nginx web folder.
		--> $ sudo cp -r /home/ec2-user/valuation-management-system-app/browser/* /usr/share/nginx/html/    ==> "/usr/share/nginx/html/" this is nginx server directory so copy here project files.
		--> $ sudo systemctl restart nginx
		
	
